### Create RxDB Hybrid In-Memory/Persistent Database (Node.js)

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/nodejs-database.html

This snippet illustrates creating an RxDB database with hybrid storage, combining the speed of in-memory operations with background persistence. It uses `getMemoryMappedRxStorage` from `rxdb-premium` and an underlying storage like FoundationDB. This approach offers performance benefits but has limitations regarding database size and potential data loss on immediate process exit.

```javascript
import { createRxDatabase } from 'rxdb';
import { getRxStorageFoundationDB } from 'rxdb/plugins/storage-foundationdb';
import { getMemoryMappedRxStorage } from 'rxdb-premium/plugins/storage-memory-mapped';

const db = await createRxDatabase({
    name: 'exampledb',
    storage: getMemoryMappedRxStorage({
        storage: getRxStorageFoundationDB({
            apiVersion: 620,
            clusterFile: '/path/to/fdb.cluster'
        })
    })
});
```

