### Enable Key Compression in RxDB Collection Schema

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/articles/zero-latency-local-first.html

Illustrates how to enable RxDB's key compression feature within a collection's schema definition. This optimization reduces storage space by replacing long field names with shorter tokens, improving storage efficiency and replication speed. The `keyCompression: true` flag is added to the schema object.

```typescript
await db.addCollections({
  logs: {
    schema: {
      title: 'log schema',
      version: 0,
      keyCompression: true,
      type: 'object',
      primaryKey: 'id',
      properties: {
        id: { type: 'string'. maxLength: 100 },
        message: { type: 'string' },
        timestamp: { type: 'number' }
      }
    }
  }
});
```

